Installing Git on:

Windows
use msysGit (http://msysgit.github.com)

Mac OSX
brew install git

Linux
sudo apt-get install git-core

=============
Configuring git:

System level configuration:
->git config --system
->stored in c:\Program files(x86)\Git\etc\gitconfig on windows

User level configuration:
->git config --global
->stored in c:\users\<name>\.gitconfig on windows

Repository level configuration:
->git config
->stored in .git/config in each repo

-----some git config options on terminal:
->git config --global user.name "Adhish"
->git config --global user.email "adi@gmail.com"
->git config --global --list                              //user.name=Adhish
                                                          //user.email=adi@gmail.com
->cat ~/.gitconfig                                        //[user]
                                                                  name=Adhish
                                                                  email=adi@gmail.com
->git config --global core.editor vim
->git config --global help.autocorrect 1                  //config option that helps to autocorrect the spelling of some command
->git statsu                                              //NOTE: status misspelled 
                                                          //continuing under the assumption that you meant "status"
->git config --global color.ui auto                                                                  
->git config --global core.autocrlf true|false|input      //can be any of these 3 values
->git config --global --list                              //user.name=Adhish
                                                          //user.email=adi@gmail.com
                                                          //core.editor=vim
                                                          //core.autocrlf=input
                                                          //help.autocorrect=1
                                                          //color.ui=auto
